  "time_ut": 1661627874,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b86\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bae\u0bcd: \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bcb\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b86\u0baa\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Asia Cup: Afghanistan beat Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Afghanistan won their Group B match against Sri Lanka in Dubai last night in the Asia Cup.",
        "Afghanistan's captain Mohammad Nabi, who won the toss of the first match of the series, announced that his team will field first.",
        "Fast bowlers Madisha Pathirana and Dilshan Madushanga made their debut for Sri Lanka.",
        "In that way, Sri Lanka, who came out to bat first, lost Kusal Mendis and Charit Azalanga to Pasalhaq Baruqi in the first over. In the next over, Padum fell to Naveen-ul-Haq in controversial fashion. Nisanga was given out by the field umpire and on review it was given as out when the paddle passed the ball and there was no strike.",
        "Bhanuka Rajapaksa and Dhanushka Gunathilaka scored consecutive runs while Gunathilaka fell to Mujeeb ur Rahman. Vanidu Hazaranga, who came next at the appointed time, also fell to Rahman. Then skipper Dasun Shanaka fell to Nabi and Rajapaksa and Mahesh Dikshana, who scored 38 (29) runs, were successively run out.",
        "In the end, Madisha Patirana also fell to Nabi and Samika Karunaratne, who fought till the end, fell to Farooqui with 31 (38) runs, losing all wickets in 19.4 overs and Sri Lanka got 105 runs.",
        "In reply, Afghanistan were bowled out for 106 runs with Rahmanullah Gurbaz's 40 (18) and Hazratullah Sazai's unbeaten 37 (28) for the loss of 2 wickets in 10.1 overs."
      ],
